.SH FORMAT REPLACEMENTS
.PP
\fB{percentage}\fR: Percentage of memory in use.\&
.PP
\fB{swapPercentage}\fR: Percentage of swap in use.\&
.PP
\fB{total}\fR: Amount of total memory available in GiB.\&
.PP
\fB{swapTotal}\fR: Amount of total swap available in GiB.\&
.PP
\fB{used}\fR: Amount of used memory in GiB.\&
.PP
\fB{swapUsed}\fR: Amount of used swap in GiB.\&
.PP
\fB{avail}\fR: Amount of available memory in GiB.\&
.PP
\fB{swapAvail}\fR: Amount of available swap in GiB.\&
.PP
\fB{swapState}\fR: Signals if swap is activated or not
.PP
